        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 5:33PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 533 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 12 miles north of Roundup to 22 miles
northwest of Billings West End, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts 40 to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Billings, Roundup, Melstone, Shepherd, Huntley, Worden,
Ballantine, Billings Heights, Lockwood, Billings West End,
Musselshell, Broadview, Klein, Acton, Comanche, Molt, Halfbreed
Lake Wildlife, Hailstone Wildlife Refuge and Crow Indian
Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
